{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JqJwka52oEshHBABeuz9bY","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# F22 Plan\n2\t\n3\t## Acceptance criteria\n4\t\n5\tFrom SPEC.md §7.3 — Trends / Insights (`/trends`):\n6\t\n7\tControls panel:\n8\t- Event name selector (autocomplete from schema)\n9\t- Measure selector: Count / Unique Users / Sum of / Avg of / Min of / Max of [property]\n10\t  - Property dropdown appears only for aggregation measures; restricted to numeric properties\n11\t- Granularity toggle: Day / Week\n12\t- Date range: preset chips (Last 7d, Last 30d, Last 90d) + custom date picker\n13\t- Breakdown selector (optional): property dropdown + limit\n14\t\n15\tChart panel:\n16\t- Recharts `LineChart` by default\n17\t- Chart type switcher (BR-301): Line / Bar / Area / Table\n18\t- Sensible defaults: Line for time series; when only one date bucket, auto-switch to Bar\n19\t\n20\t## Dependencies\n21\t\n22\tCompleted features this builds on:\n23\t\n24\t- **F1** (ClickHouse client singleton) — `src/lib/clickhouse.ts`\n25\t- **F8** (GET /api/schema) — `src/app/api/schema/route.ts`\n26\t- **F9** (In-memory schema cache) — `src/lib/schema-cache.ts`\n27\t- **F10** (GET /api/trends with count, unique_users, numeric aggregations) — `src/app/api/trends/route.ts`, `src/lib/trends.ts`\n28\t- **F11** (Breakdown and breakdown_limit in GET /api/trends) — same route, extended\n29\t- **F18** (MUI navigation shell) — `src/app/layout.tsx`, `src/components/Sidebar.tsx`\n30\t\n31\tKey files that will be imported or extended:\n32\t\n33\t- `src/app/trends/page.tsx` — existing placeholder to replace\n34\t- `src/app/api/trends/route.ts` — backend already implemented; consumed via fetch\n35\t- `src/app/api/schema/route.ts` — backend already implemented; consumed via fetch\n36\t- `src/lib/trends.ts` — `TrendsResponse`, `Series`, `SeriesPoint` types (may be imported for type-safety)\n37\t- `src/lib/schema-cache.ts` — `SchemaResponse` type (for schema fetch typing)\n38\t\n39\t## Files to create or modify\n40\t\n41\t- CREATE `src/components/trends/useTrends.ts` — custom hook: manages control state, fetches `/api/trends`, returns series data + loading/error state\n42\t- CREATE `src/components/trends/TrendsControls.tsx` — client component: event name autocomplete, measure selector, granularity toggle, date range presets + custom picker, breakdown selector + limit\n43\t- CREATE `src/components/TrendChart.tsx` — client component: renders Recharts chart with Line/Bar/Area/Table toggle; auto-switches to Bar when single bucket\n44\t- MODIFY `src/app/trends/page.tsx` — replace placeholder with full Trends page composing controls + chart\n45\t\n46\t## Implementation order\n47\t\n48\t1. **Install `recharts`** — Add the `recharts` dependency (`pnpm add recharts`). It is not currently installed but is required by the spec for chart rendering.\n49\t\n50\t2. **Create `src/components/trends/useTrends.ts`** — Custom hook managing all trends query state:\n51\t   - Control state: `eventName`, `measure`, `granularity`, `startDate`, `endDate`, `breakdown`, `breakdownLimit`\n52\t   - Defaults: measure `\"count\"`, granularity `\"day\"`, date range last 30 days, no breakdown, breakdown_limit 10\n53\t   - Fetches `/api/schema` on mount to get event names and per-event properties (with types)\n54\t   - Fetches `/api/trends` when controls change (debounced or on explicit trigger)\n55\t   - Returns `{ schema, controls, setters, series, loading, error }`\n56\t   - Derives numeric properties for the selected event from the schema response\n57\t\n58\t3. **Create `src/components/trends/TrendsControls.tsx`** — Client component rendering:\n59\t   - MUI `Autocomplete` for event name (populated from schema)\n60\t   - MUI `Select` for measure (Count, Unique Users, Sum of, Avg of, Min of, Max of) + a secondary `Autocomplete` for property name that only appears for aggregation measures (sum/avg/min/max) and is restricted to numeric properties\n61\t   - MUI `ToggleButtonGroup` for granularity (Day / Week)\n62\t   - Date range: MUI `Chip` presets (Last 7d, Last 30d, Last 90d) + two `TextField type=\"date\"` inputs for custom range\n63\t   - MUI `Autocomplete` for optional breakdown property + `TextField` for breakdown_limit\n64\t   - Receives state and setters from `useTrends` as props\n65\t\n66\t4. **Create `src/components/TrendChart.tsx`** — Client component rendering:\n67\t   - Chart type selector: MUI `ToggleButtonGroup` with Line / Bar / Area / Table options\n68\t   - Recharts `ResponsiveContainer` wrapping `LineChart`, `BarChart`, or `AreaChart` based on selection\n69\t   - For Table mode: MUI `Table` showing date rows × series columns\n70\t   - Auto-switch: when series data has only 1 date bucket, default to Bar chart\n71\t   - Multi-series support for breakdown results (one line/bar per series label)\n72\t   - Loading skeleton when data is being fetched\n73\t   - Empty state when no series data returned\n74\t\n75\t5. **Modify `src/app/trends/page.tsx`** — Replace placeholder with full page:\n76\t   - `\"use client\"` directive\n77\t   - Compose `useTrends` hook, `TrendsControls`, and `TrendChart`\n78\t   - Page title \"Trends\"\n79\t   - Layout: controls panel at top, chart panel below\n80\t\n81\t## Sprint contract\n82\t\n83\t- [ ] `pnpm test` (vitest run) → 0 failures\n84\t- [ ] `pnpm lint` (biome check) → exit 0\n85\t- [ ] `pnpm typecheck` (tsc --noEmit) → exit 0\n86\t- [ ] `pnpm build` (next build) → exit 0\n87\t- [ ] File `src/components/trends/useTrends.ts` exists and exports a `useTrends` function\n88\t- [ ] File `src/components/trends/TrendsControls.tsx` exists and exports a named `TrendsControls` component\n89\t- [ ] File `src/components/TrendChart.tsx` exists and exports a named `TrendChart` component\n90\t- [ ] File `src/app/trends/page.tsx` exists and imports `TrendChart`\n91\t- [ ] File `src/app/trends/page.tsx` exists and imports `TrendsControls`\n92\t- [ ] HTTP check: GET `http://localhost:3000/trends` → response contains `Trends`\n93\t- [ ] HTTP check: GET `http://localhost:3000/trends` → response contains `data-testid=\"trends-controls\"` or the controls container\n94\t- [ ] HTTP check: GET `http://localhost:3000/trends` → response contains `data-testid=\"trend-chart\"` or the chart container\n95\t\n96\t## Test plan\n97\t\n98\t- **Test file**: `src/components/trends/__tests__/useTrends.test.ts`\n99\t- **Module under test**: `useTrends`\n100\t- **Cases to cover**:\n101\t  - Fetches schema from `/api/schema` on mount and exposes event names\n102\t  - Fetches trends data from `/api/trends` when event name is set and date range is valid\n103\t  - Derives numeric-only properties for the selected event name from the schema\n104\t  - Sets loading to true during fetch, false on completion\n105\t  - Defaults: measure is `\"count\"`, granularity is `\"day\"`, date range is last 30 days\n106\t  - Changing event name triggers a new fetch with updated params\n107\t  - Handles fetch errors gracefully (sets error state, series remains empty)\n108\t\n109\t- **Test file**: `src/components/trends/__tests__/TrendsControls.test.tsx`\n110\t- **Module under test**: `TrendsControls`\n111\t- **Cases to cover**:\n112\t  - Renders event name autocomplete with provided event names\n113\t  - Renders measure selector with all six options (Count, Unique Users, Sum of, Avg of, Min of, Max of)\n114\t  - Property dropdown is hidden when measure is \"count\" or \"unique_users\"\n115\t  - Property dropdown appears when measure is an aggregation (sum/avg/min/max) and shows only numeric properties\n116\t  - Renders granularity toggle with Day and Week options\n117\t  - Renders date range preset chips (Last 7d, Last 30d, Last 90d)\n118\t  - Renders breakdown property selector\n119\t\n120\t- **Test file**: `src/components/__tests__/TrendChart.test.tsx`\n121\t- **Module under test**: `TrendChart`\n122\t- **Cases to cover**:\n123\t  - Renders chart type toggle with Line, Bar, Area, Table options\n124\t  - Renders empty state when series array is empty\n125\t  - Renders loading skeleton when loading is true\n126\t  - Auto-switches to Bar chart type when series data has exactly 1 data point (single bucket)\n127\t  - In Table mode, renders an MUI table with date rows and series columns\n128\t\n129\t- **Integration gap**: HTTP check for GET `/trends` rendering the full page — requires dev server\n130\t- **Integration gap**: Chart rendering with actual Recharts components — Recharts requires a real DOM with dimensions; jsdom has zero-size containers, so Recharts renders nothing. Chart rendering verification requires e2e tests.\n131\t- **Integration gap**: Full end-to-end flow (seed data → select event → verify chart shows data) — requires running ClickHouse + Next.js\n132\t\n133\t## Risks and open questions\n134\t\n135\t1. **Recharts not installed**: The spec mandates Recharts but it is not in `package.json`. The generator must run `pnpm add recharts` before implementing the chart component. If the Recharts API has changed significantly from the version assumed in training data, the generator should check the installed version's exports.\n136\t\n137\t2. **Recharts + jsdom limitations**: Recharts relies on SVG and container dimensions. In jsdom (used by vitest for component tests), `ResponsiveContainer` renders with zero width/height, so charts produce no visible SVG paths. Component tests for `TrendChart` should test control logic (chart type selection, auto-switch, empty/loading states) rather than asserting on rendered SVG elements. Full chart rendering is an integration gap.\n138\t\n139\t3. **Date picker UX**: The spec calls for \"custom date picker\" but MUI v9 date pickers require `@mui/x-date-pickers` (not installed). Using native `<input type=\"date\">` via MUI `TextField` is acceptable and avoids an extra dependency. The generator should use `TextField` with `type=\"date\"` for custom date inputs.\n140\t\n141\t4. **Breakdown limit input**: The spec shows a `breakdown_limit` parameter but doesn't specify the exact UI. A simple numeric `TextField` alongside the breakdown property selector is sufficient.\n142\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01FjzpJwSMrfMWVdRH4rZyCB","session_id":"38862b96-3a4a-408b-a2fa-59c5b33b2701","uuid":"1248e094-e96d-4f57-aa78-22b06e1dd2e9","timestamp":"2026-04-15T16:54:03.898Z"}
