{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FXhKHA4dM5iwXi6oxSBvbx","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# F22 Sprint 1 — 2026-04-15\n2\t\n3\t## Test files written\n4\t\n5\t- `src/components/trends/__tests__/useTrends.test.ts` — covers schema fetch on mount, default control values, trends fetch behavior (trigger conditions, URL params, series population), loading state, numericProperties derivation, error handling\n6\t- `src/components/trends/__tests__/TrendsControls.test.tsx` — covers event name autocomplete, all six measure options, property dropdown conditional rendering (hidden for count/unique_users, shown for sum/avg/min/max), granularity toggle (Day/Week), date range preset chips (Last 7d, Last 30d, Last 90d), breakdown selector, data-testid container\n7\t- `src/components/__tests__/TrendChart.test.tsx` — covers all four chart type toggle options (Line/Bar/Area/Table), empty state, loading skeleton, auto-switch to Bar for single-bucket data, Table mode rendering with date rows, data-testid container\n8\t\n9\t## Sprint contract results\n10\t\n11\t| Criterion | Result | Notes |\n12\t|---|---|---|\n13\t| `pnpm test` 0 failures | ✅ | 348 passing, 25 skipped (skipped = integration tests needing DB) |\n14\t| `pnpm lint` exit 0 | ✅ | 7 warnings (all pre-existing in `seed.test.ts`), no errors |\n15\t| `pnpm typecheck` exit 0 | ✅ | Clean |\n16\t| `pnpm build` exit 0 | ✅ | `/trends` appears as `○` (static) in route table |\n17\t| `src/components/trends/useTrends.ts` exists, exports `useTrends` | ✅ | |\n18\t| `src/components/trends/TrendsControls.tsx` exists, exports `TrendsControls` | ✅ | |\n19\t| `src/components/TrendChart.tsx` exists, exports `TrendChart` | ✅ | |\n20\t| `src/app/trends/page.tsx` imports `TrendChart` | ✅ | line 6 |\n21\t| `src/app/trends/page.tsx` imports `TrendsControls` | ✅ | line 7 |\n22\t| HTTP: GET `/trends` contains `Trends` | ✅ | verified in `.next/server/app/trends.html` |\n23\t| HTTP: GET `/trends` contains `data-testid=\"trends-controls\"` | ✅ | verified in built HTML |\n24\t| HTTP: GET `/trends` contains `data-testid=\"trend-chart\"` | ✅ | verified in built HTML |\n25\t\n26\t## Files created / modified\n27\t\n28\t- **CREATED** `src/components/trends/useTrends.ts` — custom hook; fetches `/api/schema` on mount, fetches `/api/trends` when `eventName` is set, exposes `controls`, `setters`, `series`, `numericProperties`, `loading`, `error`\n29\t- **CREATED** `src/components/trends/TrendsControls.tsx` — client component; event name autocomplete, native `Select` for measure (6 options), conditional property autocomplete for aggregation measures, `ToggleButtonGroup` for granularity, preset date chips + date inputs, breakdown autocomplete with limit field\n30\t- **CREATED** `src/components/TrendChart.tsx` — client component; `ToggleButtonGroup` chart type switcher (Line/Bar/Area/Table), auto-switches to Bar when all series have exactly 1 data point, Recharts charts, MUI Table for table mode, Skeleton for loading, empty state\n31\t- **MODIFIED** `src/app/trends/page.tsx` — replaced placeholder with full Trends page composing the three above\n32\t- **CREATED** `src/components/trends/__tests__/useTrends.test.ts`\n33\t- **CREATED** `src/components/trends/__tests__/TrendsControls.test.tsx`\n34\t- **CREATED** `src/components/__tests__/TrendChart.test.tsx`\n35\t\n36\t## Known gaps\n37\t\n38\t- **HTTP checks via live server not verified**: The sprint contract HTTP checks were verified against the static build output (`.next/server/app/trends.html`) rather than a running dev server, because starting a dev server requires ClickHouse to be running (via `pnpm dev`). The built HTML confirms all three criteria.\n39\t- **Recharts in jsdom**: As documented in the test plan, Recharts renders no SVG in jsdom. The `TrendChart` tests mock recharts to verify logic (auto-switch, table mode, empty/loading states) rather than SVG content.\n40\t- **MUI v9 API**: `Stack.alignItems` and `TextField.InputLabelProps`/`inputProps` do not exist in MUI v9. Fixed by using `sx={{ alignItems }}`, `Box` flex containers, and `slotProps` instead.\n41\t\n42\t## Issues logged\n43\t\n44\tNone — no spec ambiguities encountered.\n45\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01FjzpJwSMrfMWVdRH4rZyCB","session_id":"38862b96-3a4a-408b-a2fa-59c5b33b2701","uuid":"fd4058b4-c373-48fb-b5bc-0297d2a1ea8b","timestamp":"2026-04-15T16:54:03.948Z"}
